Eight people were left injured following a collision between a taxi and light motor vehicle in Pietermaritzburg on Monday.On arrival ER24 paramedics found the taxi lying on its side on the side of the road while the light motor vehicle had come to a stop a short distance away.ER24 Spokesperson Robert McKenzie said paramedics found the driver sitting inside his light motor vehicle while the occupants had already climbed out of the taxi.&#8220;Paramedics assessed the patients and found that eight from the taxi had sustained minor to moderate injuries,&#8221; said McKenzie.The patients were treated for their injuries and thereafter transported to Northdale Hospital for further treatment.The cause of the collision is not yet known.